b'Diversification is pretty sweet. Follow the link in bio to balance risk and reward in your investment portfolio. :doughnut::money_bag::doughnut::money_bag:'

b'Green. Red. Up. Down. The market never stops moving, and opportunity awaits. Don\xe2\x80\x99t let the changing colors of a volatile market keep you from investing. Tap the link in bio to learn how you could make your next move. :vertical_traffic_light:'

b'Getting your money in order can seem overwhelming, but there is no better feeling! Go from sloppy to shipshape - tap our link in bio for tips to help you tidy up your finances; it\xe2\x80\x99s not as daunting as you might think! :dollar_banknote:'
b"You could bank on your dog making you Insta-famous this Halloween. Or you could plan for a future that's a little more likely. :jack-o-lantern:"

b'Heard of the 50/15/5 rule? It\xe2\x80\x99s our simple rule of thumb for saving and spending. Aim to allocate no more than 50% of take home pay to essential expenses and 5% for short-term savings. Bucket 15% of pretax income for retirement, and you\xe2\x80\x99re on your way to a better budget. Read more at our link in bio.'
b'No one appreciates emergency savings until they need to use theirs. Click the link in bio to learn how you can prepare for unexpected expenses.'

b'Stocks, bonds, mutual funds, ETFs...when you add them all up, it seems like there are as many investments choices as stars in the sky. We help make it easy to get started no matter the size of your budget. See link in bio for more.'
b'There\xe2\x80\x99s no one right way to save money. Swipe across for our favorite tips to decide which ones work best for you, and then read more at the link in bio!'

b'New place or new ride? Don\xe2\x80\x99t pick. Prioritize. Our new app, Fidelity Spire, can help you plan, save and invest for all your goals, so you don\xe2\x80\x99t have to choose between roommates or four wheels of freedom, you can have both. Tap link in bio for more info.'

b"Figuring out whether to buy or lease a car? It's not as complicated as you might think. How far you plan to drive it, how long you plan to keep it, and how well you'll take care of it are all keys to making your decision. Visit go.fidelity.com/buyvslease to see which option may be right for you."

b'The Fidelity Mobile App lets you access your accounts whenever \xe2\x80\x93 and wherever \xe2\x80\x93 you want. And like breakfast, it\xe2\x80\x99s a great way to jump-start your day. #FidelityToolkit'
b'Saving for a house? We can suggest an investment strategy for that. Tap the link in our bio for more info on Fidelity Go, our affordable money management option. #EyesOnThePrize'

b"Stocks by the slice. Did you know with Fractional share trading you can buy a partial share? It's a good way to start investing or to get access to expensive stocks. Available today through the Fidelity mobile app. #FidelityToolkit"
b'Retirement might be a long way away, but getting the real deal now will make things easier down the road. #MoneyMyths'
b"Short and sweet\xe2\x80\x94not all goals have to be long-term. Is there anything coming up in the next couple of years that you're saving for? #FidGoals"
b'Go off leash and let a little extra savings each month add up to something bigger\xe2\x80\x94your future home.'
b"Make saving extra cash a habit. You'll be surprised how fast it adds up. #Growth"
b'Difficult times also create opportunities for young investors (or anyone 10+ years out from retirement). Sometimes, bear markets become bull markets in a short period of time. #DontFearTheBear'

b'Meet Melissa from our marketing team. Now that she\'s working from home, she can rise to meet the needs of her clients while on her quest to bake the perfect loaf. Have you been baking during your "QuaranTime"? #FidLife #FidelityAssociate'
b'Investing gives your money more potential to grow than a traditional savings account. #investing101'
b'We believe in making the complex simpler. Sip your tea while we spill the tea on how to make your money work for you.'
